annotationA: Serine/threonine-protein phosphatase beta isoform; Required for cell adhesion in non-muscle tissues and in maintenance of muscle attachment. Vital for larval development
annotationB: Ssu72 CTD phosphatase (Ssu72) is an RNA polymerase II C-terminal domain (CTD) phosphatase. Ssu72 CTD phosphatase activity is important for RNAPII transcription and termination and for gene looping. Ssu72 may also be involved in the regulation of sister chromatid cohesion
